---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Home"
description: "Landing page"
styles:
  - /css/pages/home.css
---

<section class="home-split">
  <div class="home-card home-photo" aria-label="Headshot">
    <img class="home-photo-img" src="/assets/img/headshot.jpg" alt="Headshot" />
  </div>

  <div class="home-card home-bio">
    <div class="home-bio-inner">
      <h1>Hi, I’m <span class="accent">{{ site.name }}</span>.</h1>

      <p>
        My hometown is Kathmandu, Nepal. I graduated in Fall 2021 from
        <a href="https://www.oberlin.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Oberlin College</a>
        with a degree in Computer Science (High Honors) and Mathematics.
        I then earned my M.S. in Computer Science (Machine Learning concentration) from
        <a href="https://www.gmu.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">George Mason University</a>.
        Currently, I am continuing my Ph.D. in Computer Science at
        <a href="https://vt.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Virginia Tech's</a>
        <a href="https://www.vt.edu/innovationcampus/index.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Institute for Advanced Computing</a>
        under the advisement of
        <a href="https://people.cs.vt.edu/sanmay/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dr. Sanmay Das</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
        As a researcher in AI and machine learning,
        <strong>my interests span game theory and its applications in the allocation of scarce societal resources</strong>.
        I am particularly passionate about exploring how AI can address issues of distributive justice, and I remain
        committed to investigating the implications of various policies and mechanisms in this context.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-highlights">
  <div class="mini-grid mini-grid-centered">
    <div class="mini-card">
      <div class="mini-title">Current focus</div>
      <div class="muted">Discretion as a resource in dynamic allocation</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mini-card">
      <div class="mini-title">Methods</div>
      <div class="muted">Interpretable ML, Dynamic Models, Simulation</div>
    </div>
    <div class="mini-card">
      <div class="mini-title">Now</div>
      <div class="muted">Building Tools + Writing Papers + Dissertation</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-news">
  <article class="news-card">
    <h2 class="news-heading">News</h2>

    {% if news and (news | length) > 0 %}
      <ul class="news-list">
        {% for n in news %}
          <li class="news-item">
            <div class="news-meta">
              <span class="news-date">{{ n.date }}</span>
            </div>

            <div class="news-main">
              {% if n.link %}
                <a class="news-title" href="{{ n.link }}"
                   {% if n.link | slice(0, 4) == "http" %}target="_blank" rel="noopener"{% endif %}>
                  {{ n.title }}
                </a>
              {% else %}
                <span class="news-title">{{ n.title }}</span>
              {% endif %}

              {% if n.body %}
                <div class="muted news-body">{{ n.body | mdInline | safe }}</div>
              {% endif %}
            </div>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    {% else %}
      <p class="muted">No news yet.</p>
    {% endif %}
  </article>
</section>